## MongoDB Connection
## Replace with your own connection string (never commit real credentials)
MONGO_URI=mongodb+srv://USERNAME:PASSWORD@cluster.example.mongodb.net/DB_NAME

## Server Configuration
PORT=5000
NODE_ENV=development
CLIENT_URL=http://localhost:5173
SERVER_URL=http://localhost:5000

## JWT Secret
## Generate a strong random string for production and keep it in your real .env (not committed)
JWT_SECRET=your-jwt-secret-here

## Google OAuth Configuration
## Get these from: https://console.cloud.google.com/apis/credentials
## 1. Create OAuth 2.0 Client ID (Web application).
## 2. Under "Authorized redirect URIs" add exactly: SERVER_URL + /api/auth/google/callback
##    e.g. http://localhost:5000/api/auth/google/callback (or your SERVER_URL in production).
## 3. Put the real values in server/.env (or this file if env is loaded from repo root).
GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=your-google-oauth-client-id
GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET=your-google-oauth-client-secret